## Scalability and Future Modular Expansion

Design every feature so the platform can grow without restructuring.

### Domain Areas to Support

- job seekers
- employers
- jobs and applications
- internal team and admin operations
- marketing tooling
- support tooling
- content and language management
- notifications
- WhatsApp messaging
- analytics and reporting
- payments and billing

### Expansion Rules

- Add new features as new modules under `src/modules/`
- Avoid cross-module circular dependencies
- Prefer service-to-service calls with clear interfaces
- Extract shared logic only after the second real reuse
- Keep webhook, realtime, and queue consumers in dedicated modules
- Prepare for Redis caching of expensive reads without baking cache logic into controllers
- Prepare for Socket.IO event emitters via a notification/event module

When a module grows large, split by sub-feature folders — not by technical layer at the top level.

